s self-help groups in India. In several parts of India, particularly in Orissa, women\u2019s self-help groups are being supported to procure local produce for mid-day meals for school-going children. They not only purchase fresh supplies grown by local farmers, particularly women, but also cook and serve to children. This has considerably reduced leakages.11 Integrated services in the Philippines. In 1994 the Department of Social Welfare and Devel- opment launched the Comprehensive and Integrated Delivery of Social Service (CIDSS).", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "fe7dac70-0ad5-4681-aa75-7e98f28c1147": {"__data__": {"id_": "fe7dac70-0ad5-4681-aa75-7e98f28c1147", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2008-tackling-corruption-transforming-lives", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development Report 2008: Tackling Corruption, Transforming Lives", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2008-tackling-corruption-transforming-lives", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "92f1ce44f6347d7e660e3a3da36e21017176e9280778d2a81cfa9ce411015434"}, "2": {"node_id": "f5ca666c-33aa-45db-bb59-906a2e57ed96", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-report-2008-tackling-corruption-transforming-lives", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations